{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χθών</b>, ἡ, <br /> <i>genitive</i> χθονός, <b>earth,</b> especially <b>the surface of it</b> (rarely <b>soil,</b> χθονὸς τρίμοιρον χλαῖναν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 872): poetry word (Comedy texts only in Lyric poetry or _paratragoedia_)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], very rare in Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Ki.14.15 (codex 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor), “Supp.epigram” 2.520 (from Rome)\">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]; seldom with <i>Article</i> (only when an <i>adjective</i> is added, see below 11); ἀπὸ χ. ὑψόσ᾽ ἀερθείς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.375, compare 10.149, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.349; ἐξ ἵππων ἀποβάντες ἐπὶ χθόνα 8.492, compare 11.619; ἐπὶ χθονὶ κεῖτο τανυσθείς 20.483; κατέθηκεν ἐπὶ χθονί 6.473, compare 3.89; χθονὶ φύλλα πελάσσαι 13.180 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ χ., opposed to οὐρανῷ,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.443; ζῶντος καὶ ἐπὶ χθονὶ δερκομένοιο 1.88; ἐπὶ χ. σῖτον ἔδοντες 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.222, etc.; τοὶ ἐπὶ χ. ναιετάουσι 6.153; ἄριστον ἄνδρα τῶν ἐπὶ χ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 811 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χθόνα δύμεναι to go beneath <b>the earth,</b> i.e. to die, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.411, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 151 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐτέθαπτο ὑπὸ χθονός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 11.52 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κεκευθὼς ὑπὸ χθονὸς buried, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 588; κατὰ χθονὸς κρύψαι τινά 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 24, compare “OC” 1546 (_passive_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χθονὶ γυῖα καλύψαιμι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.38; κούφα σοι χ. ἐπάνωθε πέσοι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 463 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to θάλασσα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 576 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὑπὸ χθονός, of <b>the nether world,</b> Τάρταρον.., ἧχι βάθιστον ὑπὸ χ. ἐστι βέρεθρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.14; κάτω μελαίνας χ. 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 7.10, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 72 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ ὑπὸ χ. φίλοι, i.e. those <b>in the shades below,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ch.” 833 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 65 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὦ κατὰ χθονὸς θεαί, i.e. the Erinyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 115; εἰς τοὺς ἔνερθε καὶ κάτω χ. τόπους [prev. work] 1023. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>earth,</b> i.e. <b>the world,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pr.” 139 (_anapaest meter_), “Ag.” 528; ἐπ᾽ ἔσχατα χθονός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 956. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>Earth,</b> as a goddess, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 207, “Eu.” 6. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>land, country,</b> once in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, εἴσατο δὲ χ., of Ithaca, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.352 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πολύμηλος χ., of Libya, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 9.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εὔκαρπος χ., of Sicily, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “N.” 1.14 \">Refs</a>]; frequently in Trag., frequently without <i>Article</i>, χ. Ἀσιᾶτις, Φωκέων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 61 (_anapaest meter_), 485; with _Article_, πᾶσαν τὴν Μυκηναίων χθόνα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 423; τῆς περιρρύτου χ. Αήμνου [prev. author] “Ph.” 1; τὴν Κορινθίαν χ. [prev. author] “OT” 795; τὴν ἐμὴν χ. [prev. author] “Aj.” 846 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τῆς Ἀθηναίων χ. (<i>paratragoedia</i>) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Ephippus Comicus 14.13 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; even of a <b>city,</b> τῆσδε δημοῦχοι χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1348; νόμους χθονός [prev. author] “Ant.” 368 (Lyric poetry), compare “OT” 736, 939; Comedy texts, ὦ πόλι φίλη Κέκροπος,.. οὖθαρ ἀγαθῆς χθονός 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 110 (Lyric poetry); ξένης ἀπὸ χ. 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 71 (_paratragoedia_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Sanskrit <i>locative</i> <b>k[snull]ámi</b> 'on the ground', Hittite <b>tegan</b> 'ground', Tocharian <b>tkan-</b> 'place', Ir. <b>dū</b> 'place' (<i>accusative</i> <b>don,</b> <i>dative</i> <b>dun</b>).)","strongNumber":"G9727","accentedUnicode":"χθών","shortDef":"soil","mediumDef":"soil","stepGloss":"soil","stepTransliteration":"chthōn","_step_Type":"word"}]}